            <title>[DERBY-5011] [patch] Client driver lexer to determine statement type: fix bad attempt at incrementing a variable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5011</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the client driver lexer to determine statement type, we look for token &quot;select&quot;, &quot;update&quot;, &quot;values&quot; etc. The lexer used to has a bug in its&lt;br/&gt;
handling of end-of-line comments &quot;--&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;code does&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;idx = idx++;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but this does absolutely nothing&lt;/p&gt;</description>
